The paper deals with unsupervised representation learning, which is a topic in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on nonlinear independent component analysis (ICA), which is a subfield of unsupervised learning. The paper also discusses the use of logistic regression and the development of robust methods, which are topics in statistical learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since it discusses the estimation of latent variables and causal discovery. The paper also applies the proposed method to fMRI data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
